{
  "doc_id": "7804",
  "text": "Myocyte-specific enhancer factor 2B (MEF2B) and MEF2C have distinct roles during B cell activation. MEF2C seems to be required for GC formation as a result of its role in B cell proliferation immediately after antigen stimulation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , whereas MEF2B -which, similarly to BCL-6, is highly expressed by GC B cells [CITATION_3] was shown to directly activate the transcription of BCL6 (REF. 36 ). MEF2B expression by antigen-activated B cells slightly precedes the upregulation of BCL-6 expression, which suggests that MEF2B induces BCL-6 expression in GC precursor B cells [CITATION_4] .",
